  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Game Time!\n\nWho doesn't love a good quiz? Let's build a **terminal-based quiz game** where players answer Python trivia, earn points, and try to beat their high score.\n\n### What You'll Learn\n- Dictionaries for storing questions\n- `input()` for user interaction\n- Conditional logic (if/elif/else)\n- Score tracking with variables\n- `random.shuffle()` for randomizing questions\n\n### Game Features\n- Multiple choice questions\n- Score counter and lives system\n- Color-coded right/wrong feedback\n- Final score with percentage\n\n> **Challenge yourself:** After this lesson, try adding a timer per question using the `time` module!"
  },
